<subSubSection id="D9BA65676B39FFE5FF00A937BA2D1208" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="911F36EC6B39FFE5FF00A937BEAD11E8" blockId="16.[151,1436,1301,1927]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="A3D4EAFE6B39FFE5FF00A937BE1C1160" bold="true" box="[151,281,1301,1327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This is most slender and elongate subspecies and can be distinguished from other subspecies by its pronotum flat or very slightly selliform, not concave; integument smooth, yellowish-buff with fine bluish or purplish marking and speckling; antennae dark with distinct yellow rings, equal to or slightly longer than head and pronotum together.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="911F36EC6B39FFE5FF52A997BA2D1208" blockId="16.[151,1436,1301,1927]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="A3D4EAFE6B39FFE5FF52A997BE3F1180" bold="true" box="[197,314,1461,1487]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Habitats:</emphasis>
The preferred food plant is 
<emphasis id="A3D4EAFE6B39FFE5FD1BA997BC761181" box="[652,883,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName id="56A04D6F6B39FFE5FD1BA997BC6A1181" box="[652,879,1461,1486]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">Calotropis procera</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
a common shrub throughout the Saharian belt which favours sandy soil and semi-arid conditions. The readiness to accept alternative food plants has enabled 
<emphasis id="A3D4EAFE6B39FFE5FF00AA27BE281251" box="[151,301,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Poekilocenis</emphasis>
to survive in some areas where 
<taxonomicName id="56A04D6F6B39FFE5FD29AA27BC3F1251" box="[702,826,1541,1566]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3D4EAFE6B39FFE5FD29AA27BC3F1251" box="[702,826,1541,1566]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Calotropis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is scarce or even absent. This is the most mobile member of the genus in which both sexes especially the females have proportionately longer wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
